## Limitations

The primary limitation of this report is the reliance on secondary sources, which may not fully capture the diversity of perspectives among different Native American tribes. Additionally, the historical context and changes over time in the concept of land ownership among Native Americans are complex and may not be fully represented in the available literature. Further research, including primary sources and interviews with Native American scholars, could provide a more comprehensive understanding.